Accessing information from a public database: GEO

Minimum Information About a Microarray Experiment (MIAME) is a set of guidelines developed by the Microarray Gene Expression Data (MGED). It been adopted by many journals to support an independent evaluation of results. Gene Expression Omnibus (GEO) database at the National Center for Biotechnology Information and European Bioinformatics Institute (EBI) ArrayExpress follow same standard.

Among the several R packages that can be used to access its data, GEOquery is a simple and widely accepted package.
To install

if (!require("BiocManager", quietly = TRUE)) install.packages("BiocManager")
BiocManager::install("GEOquery", force = TRUE)

Creating metadata using template: CEDAR Workbench

It is an online resource that makes it easy to collect and use metadata

It helps user to
create user-friendly, shareable forms for collecting metadata, with features like

  • share your forms and metadata

  • link your questions (fields) and possible answers (values) to controlled terms

  • view metadata responses meeting your search critieria, in several forms

  • use the Workbench Desktop interface to manage your content

  • enable intelligent metadata suggestions in your template by using a field’s Suggestions tab

Webpage: cedar.metadatacenter.org

Click on the “Register” link to

  • Create an account

Once registered,

  • Click on the Shared with Me link on the left side to find sample template
  • Try creating your own

cedarr: Accessing CEDAR using R

For installation:

devtools::install_github("earnaud/cedarr", dependencies = TRUE)

For help:

help("API response", package = "cedarr")
# ?cedarr::`API response`
